    <section id="id1171966094453">
      <title>LARGE SCALE MAPS</title>
      <para id="id5411938">1. The World</para>
      <para id="id7109094">From this picture we can deduct that the earth is round. A round map of the earth is called a globe.</para>
      <figure id="id8724896">
        <media id="id8724896_media" alt="">
          <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/Aarde_2.png" id="id8724896__onlineimage" height="327" width="327"/>
        </media>
      </figure>
      <para id="id1171955178222">Have you ever tried to cut open and flatten a deflated ball? That is why most world maps portray the earth as “flat”.</para>
      <para id="id5740498">2. Africa (my continent)</para>
      <list id="id2880803" list-type="bulleted">
        <item>The continent on which you live, is called <emphasis effect="bold">……………………………………….</emphasis></item>
        <item>Africa is the second largest continent on earth. Africa consists of 49 countries. A country is a large piece of earth within fixed borders. The borders separate one country from the other.</item>
      </list>
      <figure id="id2073171">
        <media id="id2073171_media" alt="">
          <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/Afrika_streke.png" id="id2073171__onlineimage" height="646" width="633"/>
